373
00:51:37.219 --> 00:51:40.195
You think for yourself.

374
00:51:40.218 --> 00:51:45.474
When I was eight years old. defending
Stalingrad. I didn't think for myself.

375
00:51:45.497 --> 00:51:48.395
When the motherland asked for
our lives. we gave.

376
00:51:48.418 --> 00:51:51.475
My father didn't think of
himself. he gave.

377
00:51:51.498 --> 00:51:53.418
My mother didn't think of
herself. she gave!

378
00:51:53.498 --> 00:51:56.418
My brother didn't think of
himself. he gave!

379
00:51:58.416 --> 00:52:00.498
My comrades tied a rope around
my waist

380
